txt.en: The Wargs of Draugdegil are fed foul meats to make them stronger and more vicious.

'The Wargs of Dol Guldur are more vicious and wild than any I have yet encountered. They fight with the strength of three of their kind and seem almost tireless.

'The goblin-trainers feed their Wargs foul meats when they cannot get living prey...there must be something in the meat that grants them this extraordinary strength.

'Travel north through the gate of Fennas Guldur to Draugdegil and acquire a few scraps of this meat. We must find the source of their strength if we wish to sever it.'
Draugdegil lies to the north of Helethir, just inside the gate of Fennas Guldur.
'It was a grim task, [placeholder]. You have my thanks for returning with the meat-scraps.'
Haukur is at Helethir, south from the gate of Fennas Guldur.\n\nYou should return to Haukur for your reward.
'Maybe we will find a source of their strength thanks to you, [placeholder].'
